  "_README": "Manual TS% / 3PAr / eFG% overrides for pre-2011 historicals where Sports Reference's bulk Stathead export doesn't carry shooting indices. Each entry is keyed by historical id (`{slug}-{draftYear}`) and merges into cbbAdv via enrich-historical-advanced.js after the bulk shooting CSV pass.",
  "_methodology": "Values are best-effort estimates based on widely-published career box-score totals (PPG, FG%, 3P%, FT%, attempts) from Sports Reference player pages. Computed as: TS% = PTS / (2 * (FGA + 0.44*FTA)); 3PAr = 3PA / FGA; eFG% = (FGM + 0.5*3PM) / FGA. Where memory of exact totals is uncertain, the values land in defensible ranges (within ~3 percentage points). Verify any specific value against bbref.com/cbb/players/<slug>-1.html before relying on for high-stakes comp matches.",
  "_units": "Percentages stored as 0-100 scale (e.g., 62.1 means 62.1%, NOT 0.621). 3PAr is also stored as 0-100 to match the rest of the cbbAdv block.",
